    &lt;CommentText&gt;May we firstly offer our sincere apologies for your recent Outpatient visit. We are sorry that no one was available at the reception desk to greet you or introduce themselves to you. This is not acceptable. Your feedback and concerns have been shared with the Outpatient Team. Your feedback is so important to us as we are committed to improving our services to ensure the best experience for our patients. 

However, it is common practice for Consultants to introduce themselves to patients during a consultation and we apologise that this did not happen during your consultation. In reference to the consultant asking who the partner was, it is routine practice for staff to enquire who is accompanying a patient to an appointment in order to maintain the privacy and confidentiality of our patients during hospital appointments.

The Patient Experience Team&lt;/CommentText&gt;
